<TITLE> Ex-Indian president Abdul Kalam to visit </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 12 (bdnews24.com)Former Indian president APJ Abdul Kalam will arrive in Bangladesh on July 19, on a two-day visit. Kalam, one of the architects of India's nuclear programme, is scheduled to deliver a lecture to faculty members and students of the University of Information Technology and Sciences at the Bangladesh-China Friendship Conference Centre on July 20. "Former Indian president APJ Abdul Kalam has agreed to deliver his speech as the convocation speaker," Abdul Aziz, vice-chancellor of UITS told bdnews24.com Sunday. President Zillur Rahman, chancellor of the university, will preside at the event, while advisor to the prime minister and lecturer at Harvard University Gauhar Rizvi will speak as special guest. Kalam, the 11th Indian president, was in office from July 2002 to July 2007
